{"tid":2250182,"cid":5,"subCid":11,"title":"美國總統辯論委員會:下次辯論 每個候選人係每節2分鐘開場講緊野時 會Mute另一個  防止打斷疊聲","createTime":"2020-10-20T02:38:25.000Z","updateTime":"2020-10-20T06:16:06.000Z","uid":204533,"like":0,"dislike":10,"uniUserReply":8,"replies":[{"pid":"5d1d05b9301b897758aa16b4928edcfb3574232c","tid":2250182,"uid":204533,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-10-20T02:38:25.000Z","msg":"<blockquote>The Trump campaign voiced objections to the change - made after the president repeatedly talked over both Biden and the moderator at last month&rsquo;s debate in violation of its agreed-upon rules - but said the Republican would still take part in the Thursday night event, one of his last chances to reach a large prime-time audience before voting ends on Nov. 3.<br />\n<br />\nThe Presidential Commission on Debates said <strong><span class=\"red\">each candidate&rsquo;s microphone </span></strong>at the debate in Nashville, Tennessee, <strong><span class=\"red\">would be silenced to allow the other to make two minutes of opening remarks at the beginning of each 15-minute segment of the debate. Both microphones will be turned on to allow a back-and-forth after that time.</span></strong><br />\n<br />\n<strong>&ldquo;President Trump is committed to debating Joe Biden regardless of last-minute rule changes from the biased commission in their latest attempt to provide advantage to their favored candidate,&rdquo; campaign manager Bill Stepien said.</strong><br />\n<br />\nThe Biden campaign did not immediately respond to a request for comment.</blockquote><br />\n<a href=\"https://www.reuters.com/article/us-usa-election/final-trump-biden-debate-will-feature-mute-button-after-chaotic-first-clash-idUSKBN2740FF\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Farticle%2Fus-usa-election%2Ffinal-trump-biden-debate-will-feature-mute-button-after-chaotic-first-clash-idUSKBN2740FF&d=h9s%2FmsO%2BhBO0acKdDJaYEedgoykoOisTuuABwIAScok%3D&h=41a12f6a\" 